Garden pies are a type of pie that can be obtained by baking a raw garden pie on a cooking range, requiring level 34 Cooking and granting 138 experience when successful. Players may burn the pie while baking one, resulting in a burnt pie; the burn rate while cooking these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels. It will stop burning entirely at Cooking level 68 on ranges. Alternatively, casting the Bake Pie spell from the lunar spellbook guarantees successful baking of all pies.

Garden pie heals 12 Hitpoints in total, 2 bites each healing 6, and grants a temporary skill boost to Farming by 3 levels. After eating it, a pie dish will remain.

Romily Weaklax, in the Cooks' Guild, may ask the player for a garden pie, paying 30 coins each. They do not have to be made by the player to get the reward.

Garden pies can be purchased from the Cooks' Guild Pie Shop for 24 coins.

Cabbage from Draynor Manor will not work.

Steps
1. Use a pastry dough on a pie dish to make a pie shell
2. Use a tomato on the pie shell to make a part garden pie (tomato)
3. Use an onion on the part garden pie (tomato) to make a part garden pie (onion)
4. Use a cabbage on the part garden pie (onion) to make a raw garden pie
5. Cook the raw garden pie on a range to finish a garden pie
